@node "introduction"

 @{u}@{b}Introduction@{ub}                                         @{uu}
        
   MagnifiCAD supports ARexx in several ways. You can
   use many ARexx tools to enhance the program and
   its tools.
   
   With ARexx, you can:
   
   o @{fg shine}Execute macros/scripts@{fg text} to let the scripts handle
     repetitive tasks.
   
   o @{fg shine}Record macros@{fg text} in MagnifiCAD, i.e. the program
     can record each command you execute and save
     the recordings to a script file.
   
   o Use the @{fg shine}ARexx Command Shell@{fg text} to type commands
     directly to MagnifiCAD when you are working on
     a project.
   
   o Interact with other programs from MagnifiCAD
     using the macros.

   MagnifiCAD has 41 ARexx commands with lots of
   options for virtually every tool and setting
   in the program. You can also build simple
   requesters to make the user interact with the
   scripts.
@endnode

@node "ARexxCommandShell" "The ARexx Command Shell"

 @{u}@{b}ARexx Command Shell@{ub}                                  @{uu}
   
   The ARexx Command Shell can be used to type
   commands directly to MagnifiCAD, i.e. the commands
   will be executed at once.
   
   To open the Command Shell window, choose the 
   'ARexx/ARexx Command Shell' menuitem. The window
   will open and the menuitem will be ticked, so that
   you can see if the window is open even if it is
   hidden behind other windows.
   
   To close the window, choose the 
   'ARexx/ARexx Command Shell' menuitem again, or
   click the close gadget in the window.
@endnode

@node "UsingARexxMacros" "Using ARexx macros/scripts with MagnifiCAD"

 @{u}@{b}Using ARexx Macros/Scripts with MagnifiCAD@{ub}           @{uu}
   
   Macros and Scripts can be used in different ways
   with MagnifiCAD. You can:
   
   * run a macro from within MagnifiCAD with the
     commands on the ARexx Menu.
   
   * run macros from a Shell.
@endnode

@node "description" "ARexx Command Description Synopsis"

 @{u}@{b}Command Description Synopsis@{ub}                         @{uu}

   All the ARexx commands are described in this format:

 @{fg shine}Synopsis@{fg text}
   Name of the command and all arguments. ARexx
   command names and switches are given in upper case,
   and argument values are given in lower case. Values
   are meant to be replaced by a number or a string,
   as marked by the switches. Optional arguments are
   givenin brackets.
   
 @{fg shine}Alias@{fg text}
   If a command has more than one name, these will
   be shown here. <Alias> will be omitted if there
   are no aliases for the particular command.
   
 @{fg shine}Description@{fg text}
   Describes the purpose and action of the command.
 
 @{fg shine}Arguments@{fg text}
   Describes each argument known to the command.
  
 @{fg shine}Returns@{fg text}
   Describes what the command returns. @{fg shine}Returns@{fg text} will be
   omitted if the command doesn't return anything.
   
 @{fg shine}Examples@{fg text}
   Gives example son the usage of the command and any
   parameters.
@endnode

